am players]]\n[[Category:Canadian expatriate ice hockey players in the United States]]\n[[Category:Canadian expatriate sportspeople in Poland]]\n[[Category:Canadian expatriates in the Soviet Union]]\n[[Category:Canadian ice hockey centres]]\n[[Category:Canadian ice hockey coaches]]\n[[Category:Canadian people of Polish descent]]\n[[Category:Canadian transportation businesspeople]]\n[[Category:English\u2013Polish translators]]\n[[Category:English\u2013Russian translators]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey people from Manitoba]]\n[[Category:Minneapolis Millers (IHL) players]]\n[[Category:New Westminster Royals players]]\n[[Category:New York Rangers players]]\n[[Category:Paul Loicq Award recipients]]\n[[Category:Philadelphia Flyers scouts]]\n[[Category:Polish\u2013English translators]]\n[[Category:Quebec Aces (QSHL) players]]\n[[Category:Russian\u2013English translators]]\n[[Category:Saskatoon Quakers players]]\n[[Category:Seattle Totems (WHL) players]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Nanaimo]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Winnipeg]]\n[[Category:St. Paul Saints (IHL) players]]\n[[Category:Winnipeg Maroons players]]\n", "name_user": "GiantSnowman", "label": "safe", "comment": "date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript| Cleaned up usingAutoEd", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aggie_Kukulowicz"}
{"title_page": "Indian Institutes of Information Technology", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=May 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}}\n<!-- Colors: Avoid Red-Green per WP:COLORS. Use Green-Blue instead. -->\n{{location map+|India|width=320|float=right|caption=Location of the 5 MHRD Funded IIITs (Green) and 18 PPP IIITs (Red).|relief=|places= {{Location map~|India|label='''[[Gwalior]]'''|mark=Green_pog.svg|position=left|lat=26.22|long=78.18}} \n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Allahabad]]'''|mark=Green_pog.svg|position=bottom|lat=25.45|long=81.85}} \n{{location map~|India|label='''[[Jabalpur]]'''|mark=Green_pog.svg|position=bottom|lat=23.16|long=79.94}} \n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Kanchipuram]]'''|mark=Green_pog.svg|position=right|lat=12.83|long=80.13}} \n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Sricity]]'''|mark=Red_pog.svg|position=left|lat=13.56|long=80.02}} \n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Guwahati]]'''|mark=Red_pog.svg|position=right|lat=26.18|long=91.73}} \n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Vadodara]]'''|mark=Red_pog.svg|position=left|lat=22.18|long=73.12}} \n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Kota, Rajasthan|Kota]]'''|mark=Red_pog.svg|position=left|lat=25.16|long=75.85}} \n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Tiruchirappalli]]'''|mark=Red_pog.svg|position=right|lat=10.45|long=78.42}} \n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Una, Himachal Pradesh|Una]]'''|mark=Red_pog.svg|position=right|lat=31.4684|long=76.2708}} \n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Sonipat]]'''|mark=Red_pog.svg|position=right|lat=28.9288|long=77.0913}} \n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Kalyani, West Bengal|Kalyani]]'''|mark=Red_pog.svg|position=right|lat=22.9751|long=88.4345}}\n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Lucknow]]'''|mark=Red_pog.svg|position=top|lat=26.8467|long=80.9462}} \n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Dharwad]]'''|mark=Red_pog.svg|position=left|lat=15.4589|long=75.0078}}\n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Kurnool]]'''|mark=Green_pog.svg|position=right|lat=15.83|long=78.05}} \n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Kottayam]]'''|mark=Red_pog.svg|position=left|lat=9.55|long=76.87}} \n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Manipur]]'''|mark=Red_pog.svg|position=right|lat=24.6637|long=93.9063}}\n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Nagpur]]'''|mark=Red_pog.svg|position=bottom|lat=21.1458|long=79.0882}} \n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Pune]]'''|mark=Red_pog.svg|position=right|lat=18.5204|long=73.8567}} \n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Ranchi]]'''|mark=Red_pog.svg|position=bottom|lat=23.3441|long=85.3096}} \n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Surat]]'''|mark=Red_pog.svg|position=left|lat=21.1702|long=72.8311}}\n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Bhopal]]'''|mark=Red_pog.svg|position=left|lat=23.2599|long=77.4126}}\n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Bhagalpur]]'''|mark=Red_pog.svg|position=top|lat=25.348|long=86.972}}\n{{Location map~|India|label='''[[Agartala]]'''|mark=Red_pog.svg|position=left|lat=23.8293|long=91.2778}}\n}}\n\n'''Indian Institutes of Information Technology''' ('''IIIT'''s) are a group of institutes of [[higher education]] in [[India]], focused on [[information technology]]. Five of them are established, funded and managed by the [[Ministry of Human Resource Development (India)|Ministry of Human Resource Development]]. The rest are set up on the [[public-private partnership]] (PPP) model.\n\n==Formation==\nPrior to 2010, the IIITs at [[Atal Bihari Vajpayee Indian Institute of Information Technology and Management, Gwalior|Gwalior]], [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Allahabad|Allahabad]], [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Design and Manufacturing, Jabalpur|Jabalpur]] and [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Design and Manufacturing, Kancheepuram|Kancheepuram]] were set up by the [[Ministry of Human Resource Development]] (MHRD).<ref name=\"mhrd.gov.in\">{{cite web|url=http://mhrd.gov.in/iiits|title=Institutions \u2013  Government of India, Ministry of Human Resource Development|author=|date=|work=mhrd.gov.in|accessdate=11 January 2017}}</ref> \n\nIn 2010 the ''Indian Institutes of Information Technology Bill 2010'' was introduced in [[Lok Sabha]].{{cn|date=September 2017}} The bill sought to grants the status of [[Institutes of National Importance]] (INI) upon the four IIITs. After much debate and changes, the bill was passed by the [[Parliament of India|Parliament]] on 1 December 2014{{cn|date=September 2017}} and published as ''the [[Indian Institutes of Information Technology Act, 2014]]'' on 8 December 2014, coming into effect on 5 January 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Indian Institutes of Information Technology Act, 2014|url=http://legislative.gov.in/sites/default/files/The%20Indian%20Institutes%20of%20Information%20%20Techonology%20Act%2C%202014.pdf|publisher=[[Government of India]]|accessdate=12 September 2017|date=8 December 2014|work=[[Gazette of India]]}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, a [[Indian Institute of Information Technology Design and Manufacturing, Kurnool|fifth institute]] was set up by the MHRD in Kurnool,<ref name=\"mhrd.gov.in\"/> as part as the government obligation under the [[Andhra Pradesh Reorganisation Act, 2014]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Indian Institutes of Information Technology (Amendment) Bill, 2017|url=http://www.prsindia.org/uploads/media/GST,%202017/IIIT%20%28Amendment%29%20Bill,%202017.pdf|publisher=[[Government of India]]|accessdate=12 September 2017|date=21 March 2017}}</ref> The ''Indian Institutes of Information Technology (Amendment) Act, 2017'' granted the INI status to the Kurnool institute.<ref>{{cite web|title=Indian Institutes of Information Technology (Amendment) Act, 2017|url=http://www.prsindia.org/uploads/media//IIIT2017/IIIT%20Act,%202017.pdf|publisher=[[Government of India]]|accessdate=12 September 2017|date=17 August 2017|work=[[Gazette of India]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180417172622/http://www.prsindia.org/uploads/media/IIIT2017/IIIT%20Act,%202017.pdf|archive-date=17 April 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nBesides the above fully government funded IIITs, in 2010 the [[Union Cabinet]] approved a scheme for setting up twenty more IIITs, based on the [[public-private partnership]] (PPP) model, funded by the central government, state governments and industry partners in the ratio 50:35:15.<ref name=MHRD>{{cite web|title=Setting up of Indian Institute of Information Technology|url=http://pib.nic.in/newsite/mbErel.aspx?relid=106785|website=pib.nic.in|accessdate=16 September 2017|date=16 July 2014|publisher=[[Ministry of Human Resource Development]]}}</ref> As of 2014, 23 proposals were made by 21 states (Andhra Pradesh ([[Chittoor]] & Kakinada), Assam, Bihar, Chhattisgarh, Goa, Gujarat, Haryana, Himachal Pradesh, Jharkhand, Karnataka, Kerala, Madhya Pradesh, Maharashtra (Pune & Nagpur), Manipur, Orissa, Punjab, Rajasthan, Tamil Nadu, Tripura, West Bengal and Uttar Pradesh), and 16 proposals were approved (Andhra Pradesh (Chittoor), Andhra Pradesh (Kakinada), Assam, Gujarat, Haryana, Himachal Pradesh, Karnataka, Kerala, Madhya Pradesh, Rajasthan, Tamil Nadu , Maharashtra (Pune), Uttar Pradesh, West Bengal , Manipur and Tripura).<ref name=MHRD/> {{as of|2017}} 14 of these IIITs were set up, the ones not being set up are the ones in [[Kakinada]], Andhra Pradesh and in [[Bodhjungnagar]], [[Tripura]]. In addition, in 2015 the MHRD approved an IIIT in Nagpur, Maharashtra<ref>{{cite news|last1=Choudhari|first1=Abhishek|title=HRD ministry approves IIIT for Nagpur|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/nagpur/HRD-ministry-approves-IIIT-for-Nagpur/articleshow/47289929.cms|accessdate=16 September 2017|work=[[The Times of India]]|agency=Times News Network|date=15 May 2015}}</ref> and in Ranchi, Jharkhand.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Narayan|first1=Santosh|title=Cabinet clears decks for setting up IIIT|url=http://www.dailypioneer.com/state-editions/ranchi/cabinet-clears-decks--for-setting-up-iiit.html|accessdate=16 September 2017|work=[[The Pioneer (newspaper)|The Pioneer]]|date=9 December 2015|language=en}}</ref> An IIIT in Bhagalpur, Bihar was approved in 2016.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Roshan|first1=Kumar|title=More room for education|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/1161215/jsp/bihar/story_124713.jsp|accessdate=16 September 2017|work=[[The Telegraph (Calcutta)|The Telegraph]]|date=15 December 2016}}</ref> Finally, to close the list of 20, an IIIT in Surat, Gujarat was approved and set up in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=IIIT Surat|url=http://svnit.ac.in/iiitsurat/web/about.php|website=svnit.ac.in|accessdate=16 September 2017|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181122072104/http://svnit.ac.in/iiitsurat/web/about.php|archive-date=22 November 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> {{as of|2017|9}}, these four institutes were already established, leaving only the institutes in Kakinada and Bodhjungnagar which are yet to be established.\n\nOn 9 August 2017, ''The [[Indian Institutes of Information Technology (Public-Private Partnership) Act, 2017]]'' has been notified in the [[Gazette of India]].<ref name=\"egazette.nic.in\">{{cite web|url=http://egazette.nic.in/WriteReadData/2017/177925.pdf|title=The Indian Institutes of Information Technology (Public-Private Partnership) Act, 2017|date=9 August 2017|work= egazette.nic.in| accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref> The Act confers the status of Institutes of National Importance to fifteen IIITs set up on the public-private partnership (PPP) mode in [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Vadodara|Vadodara]], [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Guwahati|Guwahati]], [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Sri City|Sri City]], [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Kota|Kota]], [[Indian Institute of Information Technology Tiruchirappalli|Tiruchirapalli]], [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Kalyani|Kalyani]], [[Indian Institute of Information Technology Una|Una]], [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Sonepat|Sonepat]], [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Lucknow|Lucknow]], [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Kottayam|Kottayam]], [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Manipur|Senapati (Manipur)]], [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Dharwad|Dharwad]], [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Pune|Pune]], [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Nagpur|Nagpur]] and [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Ranchi|Ranchi]].\n\nThe three IIITs set up under the PPP model in 2017, namely institutes in [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Surat|Surat]], [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Bhopal|Bhopal]] and [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Bhagalpur|Bhagalpur]], were not mentioned in the 2017 PPP act, nor were the institutes in Kakinada and Bodhjungnagar.\n\nIn 2018, the [[Government of Tripura]] approved {{INRConvert|50.67|c}} for the establishment of IIIT Bodhjungnagar, which was stalled since 2012, covering {{INRConvert|5.82|c}} which were missing from private sources under the PPP model.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Deb |first1=Debraj |title=Rs 50cr approved for IIIT in Tripura |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/states/north-east/rs-50cr-approved-for-iiit-in-tripura/cid/1446553 |accessdate=18 January 2019 |work=[[Telegraph India]] |date=13 April 2018 |language=en}}</ref> The institution was set to start classes in the 2018\u20132019 academic session from the [[NIT Agartala]] campus.<ref>{{cite news |title=IIIT to start classes in Tripura this year |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/agartala/iiit-to-start-classes-in-tripura-this-year/articleshow/63758204.cms |accessdate=18 January 2019 |work=[[The Times of India]] |date=14 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016 the central government gave in-principle approval for an IIIT in [[Raichur]], Karnataka.<ref>{{cite news |title=In-principle approval given for IIIT in Raichur |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/%E2%80%98In-principle-approval-given-for-IIIT-in-Raichur%E2%80%99/article16807336.ece |accessdate=8 October 2019 |work=[[The Hindu]] |date=15 December 2016 |language=en-IN}}</ref> In 2018, the MHRD clarified that the Raichur institute will replace the Kakinada one, and asked the state government to assign land for the institute, planning to make the institute functional by the following year.<ref>{{cite news |title=MHRD confirms IIIT at Raichur |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/mhrd-confirms-iiit-at-raichur/article22515693.ece |accessdate=8 October 2019 |work=[[The Hindu]] |date=25 January 2018 |language=en-IN}}</ref> However, since the land was not acquired, in 2019 the MHRD decided to shift the IIIT to [[Hyderabad]], Telangana.<ref>{{cite news |title=IIIT goes to Telangana |url=https://bangaloremirror.indiatimes.com/bangalore/others/iiit-goes-to-telangana/articleshow/70386498.cms |accessdate=8 October 2019 |work=[[Bangalore Mirror]] |date=26 July 2019 |language=en}}</ref> It started its academic activity in August 2019 from temporary campus of [[Indian Institute of Technology Hyderabad]], Telangana.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ullas |first1=Sruthy Susan |title=IIIT-Raichur may soon shift to its hometown |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bengaluru/iiit-raichur-may-soon-shift-to-its-hometown/articleshow/73281332.cms |accessdate=4 March 2020 |work=[[The Times of India]] |date=16 January 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Additional proposed IIITs ==\nIn 2020 Prime Minister lead Union Cabinet has been approved to setup new IIIT in [[Agartala]], [[Tripura]] alongside 4 new IIIT under [[Public-Private Partnership|PPP]] mode.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/education/article/cabinet-approves-iiit-amendment-bill-5-iiits-to-get-ini-status-to-confer-b-tech-degrees/550076|title=Cabinet approves IIIT Amendment Bill \u2013 5 IIITs to get INI Status, to confer B.Tech degrees 09:04 IST|last=Khurana|first=Kanika|date=6 February 2020|work=[[Times Now]]|access-date=7 February 2020|url-status=live|language=English}}</ref>\n\n==Admission==\nAdmissions into undergraduate programmes in IIITs for 4,000 seats are through the [[Joint Seat Allocation Authority]] and [[JEE-Main]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/1170621/jsp/frontpage/story_157994.jsp|title=More seats in new IITs 387 additional BTech berths on offer this year}}</ref>\n\n== List of IIITs ==\nThe Indian Institute of Information Technology are located in:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ IIITs and locations, sorted by date of establishment\n|-\n! Name  !! Short name \n!Established!! Mode \n! State/UT\n|-\n| [[Atal Bihari Vajpayee Indian Institute of Information Technology and Management, Gwalior]]|| ABV-IIITM Gwalior\n|1997|| MHRD || [[Madhya Pradesh]]\n|-\n| [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Allahabad]]|| IIITA \n|1999|| MHRD ||[[Uttar Pradesh]]\n|-\n| [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Design and Manufacturing, Jabalpur]]|| IIITDMJ \n|2005|| MHRD ||[[Madhya Pradesh]]\n|-\n| [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Design and Manufacturing, Kancheepuram]]|| IIITDM Kancheepuram\n|2007|| MHRD ||[[Tamil Nadu]]\n|-\n| [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Sri City]] || IIITS\n| 2013 || PPP ||[[Andhra Pradesh]]\n|-\n| [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Guwahati]] || IIITG\n| 2013 || PPP ||[[Assam]]\n|-\n| [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Vadodara ]] || IIITV\n| 2013 || PPP ||[[Gujarat]]\n|-\n| [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Kota]] || IIITK\n| 2013 || PPP ||[[Rajasthan]]\n|-\n| [[Indian Institute of Information Technology Tiruchirappalli]] || IIITT\n| 2013 || PPP ||[[Tamil Nadu]]\n|-\n| [[Indian Institute of Information Technology Una]] || IIITU\n| 2014 || PPP ||[[Himachal Pradesh]]\n|-\n| [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Sonepat]] || IIIT Sonepat\n| 2014 || PPP ||[[Haryana]]\n|-\n| [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Kalyani]] || IIIT Kalyani\n| 2014 || PPP ||[[West Bengal]]\n|-\n| [[Indian Institute of Information Technology, Lucknow